29:48.840 --> 29:51.071
Like Ella Fitzgerald!
♪ Doo, doo, doo, doo, doo ♪

29:51.120 --> 29:53.032
That's...
I got five rock-head boys.

29:53.080 --> 29:54.673
- I can't stand them.
- But...

29:54.720 --> 29:56.837
Now, what you want to do is,
you want to bounce Ella.

29:56.880 --> 29:58.360
Don't pat.
Bounce Ella.

29:58.440 --> 30:00.636
Bounce that burp
right out of Ella.

30:00.680 --> 30:02.911
I bet you that wife of yours
is patting.

30:02.960 --> 30:04.474
That's why she got that colic.

30:06.560 --> 30:07.856
- That right over there.
- The pink one?

30:07.880 --> 30:08.880
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

30:08.881 --> 30:11.157
Is your wife breastfeeding?

30:11.200 --> 30:13.510
- Is she what?
- Does she breastfeed?

30:13.560 --> 30:15.472
- Oh, no.
- No?

30:15.520 --> 30:17.591
And what kind of formula
are you using?

30:17.640 --> 30:19.916
Hydrolyzed, soy, casein?

30:22.560 --> 30:24.392
I wouldn't use that casein.

30:24.440 --> 30:26.159
That casein,
something wrong with it.

30:26.200 --> 30:27.998
They trying to trick us,

30:28.040 --> 30:31.317
because those babies get sick,
and probably cause that colic.

30:31.360 --> 30:33.556
I would use the hydrolyzed
because the hydrolyzed

30:33.600 --> 30:35.193
is better
on the digestive system.

30:35.240 --> 30:38.756
Thank you very much.

30:38.800 --> 30:40.234
Well, good luck!

30:45.920 --> 30:47.434
Ah!

30:56.760 --> 30:59.400
♪ Malibu to San Diego ♪

30:59.440 --> 31:02.399
♪ San Francisco, San Mateo ♪

31:06.880 --> 31:09.349
♪ Oh, oh, up in California ♪

31:09.400 --> 31:11.835
♪ We've been up in California ♪

31:11.880 --> 31:12.880
♪ Oh, oh ♪

31:23.040 --> 31:25.430
Hi, Ella.

31:25.480 --> 31:28.200
You're okay.
You're okay.

31:42.600 --> 31:44.193
Hmm.

33:06.800 --> 33:08.553
Hi, Ella.

33:11.280 --> 33:14.079
Okay.
Whoa! Whoa. Whoa.

33:14.120 --> 33:17.670
Are you... Are you okay?
Are you okay?

33:17.720 --> 33:20.315
You are?
That scared me.

33:20.360 --> 33:21.794
But you're okay?

33:21.840 --> 33:24.071
I thought you were
going to hit your head.

33:24.120 --> 33:26.271
♪ Washing is fun ♪

33:26.320 --> 33:27.913
Okay. Whoa. Whoa, whoa.

33:27.960 --> 33:30.270
Hey.
Don't cry.

33:30.360 --> 33:34.070
Do you want to know
something funny?

33:34.120 --> 33:37.431
I've lived in California
almost 25 years,

33:37.480 --> 33:40.154
and I've never been
to the beach.

33:41.400 --> 33:43.437
I had kind of an idea.

33:46.640 --> 33:49.951
Would you want to spend the day
at the ocean with me?

33:52.280 --> 33:54.033
Is that a yes?

33:54.080 --> 33:56.720
Yeah?

33:56.760 --> 33:58.433
You want to?

33:58.480 --> 34:00.995
Yeah? You do?

34:01.040 --> 34:02.235
I do, too!

34:02.280 --> 34:05.159
There's a train!
We can take a train.

34:19.440 --> 34:20.998
That's the ocean.

34:23.320 --> 34:24.913
Look, Ella.

35:00.200 --> 35:01.759
Here.

35:08.040 --> 35:11.431
Did I ever tell you that my dad
used to collect stamps?

35:11.480 --> 35:13.756
He had an incredible collection.

35:13.840 --> 35:16.639
Do you know that they have
a different stamp

35:16.680 --> 35:19.149
for every animal?

35:19.200 --> 35:20.953
Yeah.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.152
I'll always remember
going into his study

35:24.200 --> 35:26.840
where he kept his library
of stamp books.

35:26.880 --> 35:30.999
The place was covered with ash
because he smoked all the time.

35:31.040 --> 35:32.872
But we would sit in there,

35:32.920 --> 35:35.833
and we would write down all the
catalog numbers of the stamps

35:35.880 --> 35:37.678
that we wanted to
to mail away for.

35:37.720 --> 35:41.396
And I used to love
watching him open the envelopes

35:41.440 --> 35:43.352
when they arrived

35:43.400 --> 35:46.393
because they always were
exactly the same,

35:46.440 --> 35:49.274
in these brown wax envelopes

35:49.320 --> 35:51.391
with the exact
same handwriting...

35:51.440 --> 35:55.673
Philip Caruso
from Appleton, Wisconsin.

35:55.720 --> 36:01.398
But you never knew what stamp
was gonna be inside, you know?

36:01.440 --> 36:04.638
So it was...
it was really exciting.

36:06.240 --> 36:08.072
Yeah.

36:08.120 --> 36:11.875
And then he would separate all
his from the ocean-life stamps,

36:11.920 --> 36:13.957
and then he would
give those to me,

36:14.000 --> 36:17.755
and he would explain their Latin
names and where they came from.

36:21.680 --> 36:23.717
His hands used to shake.

36:25.080 --> 36:30.075
You could see it
when he was mounting the stamps

36:30.120 --> 36:33.796
under the magnifying glass,
you know?

36:33.840 --> 36:36.480
Or you could see it
in his handwriting.

36:36.520 --> 36:39.399
Or you'd hear it
in the ice in his whiskey.

36:41.800 --> 36:44.076
But you would like him, though.

36:46.200 --> 36:49.557
And he would like you.
He would.

36:49.600 --> 36:53.116
Do you think that you would like
to collect stamps? Hmm?

36:55.120 --> 36:58.875
I wonder
what your favorite animal is.

36:58.920 --> 37:03.039
"The world isn't split into
good people and Death Eaters.

37:03.080 --> 37:07.916
We've all got both
light and dark inside of us.

37:07.960 --> 37:11.874
What matters is the part
we choose to act on.

37:11.920 --> 37:14.355
That's who we really are."

37:14.400 --> 37:15.959
Yeah.

37:16.000 --> 37:17.320
What?

37:17.360 --> 37:19.829
Oh. Sorry.
You dropped your spoon.

37:48.360 --> 37:50.477
Oh, my God.

37:50.520 --> 37:53.115
Are you okay?

37:53.160 --> 37:55.550
I'm so sorry.
Shh.

37:55.600 --> 37:57.432
I'm so sorry.
I'm so sorry.

37:57.480 --> 37:59.199
I'm so sorry.

37:59.240 --> 38:01.994
♪ Merrily, merrily, merrily ♪

38:02.040 --> 38:03.156
♪ Life is but... ♪

38:09.720 --> 38:12.838
Ella,
I'm so sorry.

38:20.840 --> 38:23.309
Please take a seat
and fill out this form.

38:24.720 --> 38:27.554
But I'm... I'm not here
for me.

38:27.600 --> 38:29.273
I'm here for Ella.

38:29.320 --> 38:30.834
You still need to fill out
the form

38:30.880 --> 38:33.475
before I can process
either you or your daughter.

38:34.160 --> 38:35.594
Okay.

38:55.080 --> 38:58.278
Sir?
Are you Mr. Millings?

38:58.320 --> 38:59.320
Uh, yeah.

38:59.360 --> 39:00.760
Mm-hmm.

39:00.800 --> 39:03.076
I hear you may have found
this little angel.

39:03.120 --> 39:04.873
Yeah.

39:04.920 --> 39:06.400
I found her.

39:06.440 --> 39:08.352
Where did you find her?

39:08.400 --> 39:11.871
Um...

39:11.920 --> 39:13.559
In a dumpster.

39:19.400 --> 39:22.393
- Hi.
- Her name is Ella.

39:22.440 --> 39:24.238
I see.

39:24.280 --> 39:26.795
Hi, Ella.
Ohh!

39:26.840 --> 39:29.071
Is that how you hit your head,
sweetie pie?

39:33.160 --> 39:34.435
Okay.

39:34.480 --> 39:36.836
Uh, now, with all
abandoned-child cases,

39:36.880 --> 39:41.511
it's mandatory for both the LAPD
and the DCFS to be involved.

39:41.560 --> 39:44.200
Both have been notified
and should be here shortly.

39:44.240 --> 39:46.914
But I'm also going to have to
take little Ella

39:46.960 --> 39:49.759
to be looked at, okay?

39:49.800 --> 39:53.271
What, you mean...
you mean now?

39:53.320 --> 39:55.277
Yes.
I mean now.

39:55.320 --> 39:56.754
But the authorities

39:56.800 --> 39:58.837
and the Department of
Child and Family Services

39:58.880 --> 40:00.519
will need you to stay here.

40:00.560 --> 40:02.552
They just need to ask you
a few questions

40:02.600 --> 40:04.637
about how you found
the poor thing.

40:05.280 --> 40:07.476
Um...

40:07.520 --> 40:09.239
Will I...

40:10.840 --> 40:13.196
Will I be able
to see her again?

40:13.240 --> 40:16.119
I can't answer that question
at this time.

40:16.160 --> 40:18.994
Oh, but here are the people
who can.

40:20.280 --> 40:22.033
Come on, sweetie.

40:22.080 --> 40:23.639
Yes, yes, yes.

40:23.680 --> 40:27.151
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, yeah.

40:27.200 --> 40:29.920
Um, oh, well, this is hers.

40:29.960 --> 40:31.440
Her stuffy.

40:31.480 --> 40:32.976
No, I need to see the bag
and anything else

40:33.000 --> 40:34.656
that might have been
in the crime scene, sir.

40:34.680 --> 40:36.399
Oh, no.
There's no crime scene.

40:36.440 --> 40:39.274
It's not...
This is just her walrus.

40:41.200 --> 40:43.056
Yeah, I know, but this it's
not... not a crime scene.

40:43.080 --> 40:45.037
It's... It's just...
It's your walrus.

40:45.080 --> 40:47.151
Do you want your walrus?

40:48.840 --> 40:50.638
I know.

40:53.240 --> 40:54.594
I'll take this.

40:54.680 --> 40:57.878
Oh!
Shh, shh, shh.

40:57.920 --> 41:00.992
- Yeah.
- Bye, Ella.

41:03.360 --> 41:06.114
I'm Officer Cato.
This is Mrs. Deeks from DCFS.

41:06.160 --> 41:09.676
We need to ask you
some questions.

41:09.720 --> 41:11.951
- Okay.
- All right.

41:12.000 --> 41:16.392
Um, where did you say
you found the child?

41:16.440 --> 41:18.033
Dumpster.

41:18.120 --> 41:20.351
A lot of dumpsters out there.
Any one in particular?

41:22.520 --> 41:27.675
Um, the one by where I work.
In the back.

41:27.720 --> 41:32.670
And what time did you say
you found her this morning?

41:32.760 --> 41:34.513
Um...

41:36.840 --> 41:39.958
It was...
I don't remember.

41:40.000 --> 41:41.116
Early.

41:41.160 --> 41:42.879
Okay.

41:42.920 --> 41:46.436
Can you, um,
walk us through the event?

41:52.720 --> 41:55.633
I know this must be hard for
you, Mister, uh, Millings,

41:55.680 --> 41:59.754
but we need you to be very
specific about what happened.

41:59.800 --> 42:01.837
How did you know
she was in the dumpster?

42:04.880 --> 42:07.076
'Cause I heard her.

42:07.120 --> 42:08.679
You heard her crying?

42:11.880 --> 42:13.200
And then?

42:14.560 --> 42:16.791
And then...

42:18.400 --> 42:23.953
I heard her crying,
and I opened the dumpster,

42:24.000 --> 42:26.515
and I...

42:26.560 --> 42:30.554
I looked in, um...

42:32.800 --> 42:34.029
Mr. Millings...

42:36.280 --> 42:38.431
It's perfectly normal
for an experience like this

42:38.480 --> 42:39.834
to be traumatic.

42:39.880 --> 42:42.156
And not just for her
but for you as well.

42:42.200 --> 42:43.998
You're both victims.

42:45.520 --> 42:48.797
It's okay.
Just tell us what you remember.

42:53.160 --> 42:55.914
You, um...
You called her Ella.

42:55.960 --> 42:58.919
How did you know her name?
Or is that a name you gave her?

43:01.400 --> 43:05.599
She was in... in...
in the bag, in... in this bag,

43:05.640 --> 43:07.199
and there was a note.

43:07.240 --> 43:10.199
Okay, good.
What did the note say?

43:11.800 --> 43:13.951
It said,
"Her name was Ella."

43:15.560 --> 43:17.279
And where's the note?

43:24.360 --> 43:26.556
I don't know.

43:26.600 --> 43:28.353
I...

43:30.400 --> 43:32.437
- It's okay.
- I think I lost it.

43:35.040 --> 43:37.509
Is there a number I can
reach you at, Mr. Millings?

43:39.400 --> 43:43.758
You can come
to my place if you want.

43:46.680 --> 43:48.990
Can you, um, write down
that information

43:49.040 --> 43:50.713
along with your name
and address?

43:53.760 --> 43:56.719
Do you think that, uh...

43:56.760 --> 43:58.513
Do you think Ella
is gonna be okay?

43:58.560 --> 43:59.789
- Yes.
- Yeah?

43:59.840 --> 44:02.674
Yes, Ella will be
very well taken care of.

44:02.720 --> 44:03.995
I promise.

44:04.040 --> 44:05.633
She's a ward of the state now

44:05.680 --> 44:07.616
within the Department of
Children and Family Services,

44:07.640 --> 44:09.996
and we'll do our best to track
down someone in her family.

44:10.040 --> 44:12.600
But if not, she'll be placed
in proper foster care

44:12.640 --> 44:14.597
and then adoption.

44:14.640 --> 44:19.192
It's a bit of a process
unfortunately, but...

44:19.240 --> 44:21.357
Well, I could take care of her,
you know?

44:21.400 --> 44:24.711
I mean, I could...
I could adopt her.

44:24.760 --> 44:25.876
I mean...

44:28.960 --> 44:31.236
That is
incredibly sweet of you.

44:31.280 --> 44:34.159
Unfortunately, that's out of
my power or jurisdiction

44:34.200 --> 44:38.797
to decide whether or not you
qualify to foster this child.

44:38.840 --> 44:42.231
But I understand the urge
to want to help. I do.

44:42.280 --> 44:44.272
And you can help us
by giving us

44:44.320 --> 44:46.880
all the information
you have now.

44:46.920 --> 44:49.276
If anything comes to you,

44:49.320 --> 44:51.312
please feel free
to call me, okay?

44:53.400 --> 44:54.675
Okay.

45:46.920 --> 45:49.196
Russ.
Russ!

45:49.240 --> 45:50.276
Huh?

45:50.320 --> 45:53.074
Um, they want to talk to you.

45:55.280 --> 45:59.069
Hey, you mind stepping out and
chatting with us for a second?

45:59.520 --> 46:01.079
It's okay.
We don't bite.

46:05.400 --> 46:10.191
So, uh, the report says that you
found the baby in a dumpster.

46:13.640 --> 46:16.280
- The dumpster here at work?
- Yeah, that one.

46:19.040 --> 46:21.271
Okay, and in your statement,
it says that this incident

46:21.320 --> 46:24.074
occurred yesterday morning.

46:30.800 --> 46:34.032
Okay, Mr. Millings, do you mind
taking us over to that dumpster?

46:39.800 --> 46:43.237
You just found her in a gym bag
with a note, nothing else?

46:43.320 --> 46:45.357
What about that walrus,
though?

46:47.600 --> 46:49.080
We checked
with your management,

46:49.120 --> 46:51.680
and they say you didn't work
yesterday morning.

46:51.720 --> 46:55.077
In fact, they say you haven't
worked since Wednesday night.

46:56.680 --> 46:58.956
What you been doing since then,
Mr. Millings?

47:02.560 --> 47:04.119
We know about your record.

47:04.160 --> 47:05.514
You're still a parolee

47:05.560 --> 47:06.896
in the good state of California,
aren't you?

47:06.920 --> 47:08.056
Bet you're
counting the days

47:08.080 --> 47:10.117
till you can leave the state.

47:10.160 --> 47:13.676
Hey, um, can I get
that key back?

47:14.400 --> 47:16.416
You weren't here on Friday.
It's last week's paycheck.

47:16.440 --> 47:17.656
And I'm gonna have to call
the higher-ups

47:17.680 --> 47:18.830
about this whole baby thing.

47:18.880 --> 47:21.793
So you being
an ex-con and all,

47:21.840 --> 47:23.240
they're gonna want to know.

47:25.880 --> 47:27.109
See, my partner and I,

47:27.160 --> 47:28.514
we don't think
you found her here.

47:28.560 --> 47:30.199
We think you found her
somewhere else.

47:30.240 --> 47:31.976
We also don't think
you found her yesterday.

47:32.000 --> 47:34.959
You do know you can't take home
abandoned children, right?

47:35.000 --> 47:37.834
We know about your record.

47:37.880 --> 47:40.395
20 years in Folsom.

47:40.440 --> 47:42.136
Hell, you're still a parolee
in the good state

47:42.160 --> 47:43.674
of California, aren't you?

47:43.720 --> 47:45.757
But you're not
going anywhere, right?

48:00.320 --> 48:03.119
Have a good one.
Next.

48:09.520 --> 48:12.274
Do you have a bus to Wyoming?

48:12.320 --> 48:14.039
Okay, sir.

48:14.080 --> 48:15.719
Where in Wyoming
would you like to go?

48:15.760 --> 48:19.834
112 Trigood Avenue, Casper,
Wyoming 82602.

48:19.880 --> 48:21.758
Well, all right.

48:21.800 --> 48:24.235
Is that, uh,
round trip or one way?

48:24.280 --> 48:26.840
Uh, one way.

48:26.880 --> 48:30.271
And when
do you plan on leaving?

48:30.320 --> 48:31.356
Now.

50:22.200 --> 50:24.317
Denver.

50:24.360 --> 50:26.238
Just give me a second.

50:31.440 --> 50:33.671
I just had it.
I literally just had it.

50:36.200 --> 50:39.079
Just put my suitcase
on the bus while I find it.

50:39.120 --> 50:40.440
I know I just had it.

50:40.480 --> 50:41.976
I can't let you on
without a ticket.

50:42.000 --> 50:44.071
No, I know that!
I just...

50:44.120 --> 50:46.077
I mean, I just had it!

50:46.120 --> 50:48.351
Where...

50:48.440 --> 50:53.037
What the fuck?!
Ugh!

50:53.080 --> 50:54.992
Ticket or no,
you can't come on the bus

50:55.040 --> 50:56.474
if you're gonna be
a disturbance.

50:56.520 --> 50:58.398
I'm not...

50:58.440 --> 50:59.999
She's stressed out.

51:00.040 --> 51:03.158
I'm not gonna disturb anyone.
If you could just...

51:03.200 --> 51:05.157
Could it be in your pocket?

51:05.200 --> 51:07.271
No, it is not in my pocket!

51:13.080 --> 51:14.673
Thank you.

51:15.720 --> 51:17.996
I'll push your bag for you.

52:03.440 --> 52:04.874
Can I fucking help you?

52:55.440 --> 52:56.999
$9.75.

52:57.640 --> 53:00.633
Oh. Um...

53:00.680 --> 53:03.798
W-What about no chips?

53:06.440 --> 53:07.556
$6.95.

53:07.600 --> 53:09.114
Yeah. Yeah.

53:19.520 --> 53:21.079
Thank you.

53:25.560 --> 53:27.153
I'll put them back.

53:37.240 --> 53:40.233
You're welcome.
Don't choke.

53:43.960 --> 53:45.110
Thank you.

53:48.440 --> 53:50.716
Champ, you didn't listen.

53:50.760 --> 53:52.638
Oh, my God.

53:54.120 --> 53:56.157
Have some of your...
your drink.

53:56.200 --> 53:58.999
Um, I am.

53:59.040 --> 54:00.315
Is that better?

54:00.360 --> 54:01.396
Mm-hmm.

54:04.040 --> 54:05.156
Don't die on me.

54:11.360 --> 54:12.476
I'm okay.

54:35.200 --> 54:36.953
Would you like a sandwich?

54:37.000 --> 54:38.150
What?

54:40.920 --> 54:43.196
What kind of sandwich?

54:43.240 --> 54:45.880
Mm, mustard and mayo.

54:47.600 --> 54:50.957
You're gonna make me a mustard
and mayonnaise sandwich?

54:51.000 --> 54:53.071
Mm-hmm, i-if you want.
If you don't want...

54:53.120 --> 54:54.918
No, yeah, sure.

54:54.960 --> 54:56.553
Let's go, bro.

54:56.600 --> 54:58.637
Make me that mustard
and mayonnaise sandwich.

55:02.400 --> 55:03.993
Okay.

55:25.080 --> 55:26.639
Wait, can you
cut the crusts off?

55:26.680 --> 55:28.120
- Mm-hmm.
- No, I'm fucking with you.

55:28.160 --> 55:29.833
I'm kidding.

55:29.880 --> 55:31.519
No, it looks...
it looks amazing.

55:31.560 --> 55:33.631
That's...

55:33.680 --> 55:34.909
Okay.

55:57.320 --> 55:58.549
Mm.

56:02.400 --> 56:04.960
♪ On the brand-new moon ♪

56:05.000 --> 56:08.516
♪ Where you stumbled around
in a tree ♪

